text:
North Korea Says It Will Reject Malaysia’s Autopsy Results Announcement comes days after death of Kim Jong Nam, half brother of North Korean leader By Google+ Updated Feb. 17, 2017 4:19 p.m. ET 
KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia—North Korea said it would reject the results of a postmortem examination conducted by Malaysia on one of its citizens who died in Kuala Lumpur this week. 
The announcement was made for the first time since Kim Jong Nam, the estranged half brother of North Korean leader Kim Jong Un, was killed in Malaysia on Monday. The statement didn’t identify the deceased North Korean.
